  "body": "<!-- Please use this template while reporting a bug and provide as much info as possible. Not doing so may result in your bug not being addressed in a timely manner. Thanks!\r\n\r\nIf the matter is security related, please disclose it privately via https://kubernetes.io/security/\r\n-->\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nThe [old volume limits predicates](https://github.com/bertinatto/kubernetes/blob/b5dfcf357a358ae48591ed7fda39ff72791f7fbe/pkg/scheduler/algorithm/predicates/predicates.go#L86-L98) are now deprecated in favor of the [MaxCSIVolumeCountPred predicate](https://github.com/bertinatto/kubernetes/blob/b5dfcf357a358ae48591ed7fda39ff72791f7fbe/pkg/scheduler/algorithm/predicates/predicates.go#L100).\r\n\r\nRecently it was [found out](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/80247#issuecomment-512830032) that the old predicates don't check whether the provisioner of an **unbound volume** is the one that they should be counting. As a result, these predicates always assume that an unbound volume is theirs, counting it towards the limit.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nCreate a pod with [more than 16](https://github.com/bertinatto/kubernetes/blob/b5dfcf357a358ae48591ed7fda39ff72791f7fbe/pkg/scheduler/algorithm/predicates/predicates.go#L110-L116) unbound volumes. One of the old predicates will prevent the pod from being scheduled.\r\n\r\n/sig storage\r\nCC @jsafrane @gnufied ",
